	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You should use a transistor to bring the level up.
<br />
<br />Connect the video through a small cap to a NPN's base, connect a 22k pull up resistor also to the base. Connect the collector to VCC and the emitter to video out and a 22k pulldown to GND.
<br />
<br />You should also use a cap in series with the audio to remove any DC offset (I don't know if there is any.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
